&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;i&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;j&lt;/code&gt; are very popular variable names (see e.g., &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4137785/why-are-variables-i-and-j-used-for-counters&quot;&gt;this question&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/454303/why-are-we-using-i-as-a-counter-in-loops&quot;&gt;this one&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For example, in loops:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-matlab s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-matlab&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-built_in&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;=&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-number&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-number&quot;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;,
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;% Do something...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As indices into a matrix:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-matlab s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-matlab&quot;&gt;mat(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-built_in&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-built_in&quot;&gt;j&lt;/span&gt;) = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-number&quot;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why &lt;em&gt;shouldn&apos;t&lt;/em&gt; they be used as variable names in MATLAB?&lt;/p&gt;
